column5: congrats on your 133 hour virgin, buster .  nice pick-up man. .. enjoy

Not to hyjack this thread but are we talking bout a De Tomaso Pantera???  They came with 351 cu in engines.  No big blocks.  I may be wrong but when it comes to cars, not usually.  My buddy had one as well.  They are mid engine and I don't think they have enoyugh room to shoehorn in a bigblock.  As for the boat, congrats.  SUCK MY WAKE would be a good name for her.

HOLY MAN the dreams i had last night  .........  Her name is BAD MANNERS,  thats the name it has and came with so I think I'll keep it, dont think its good luck to change the name of a vessel? I dont know,someone told me that once lol ,Iam four leaf clover Irish,....., you can bring all the bannanas you want tho  .
Looks fast and a   demon. I gotta think like Roy and Wayne though...how does it troll and is there room for a 6 pack of Bud while it gets the throttle?
Never change the name of a vessel, bad luck for sure Buster. I bet she sounds so sweet coming out of them thru hull exhaust. The big block thunder.
Picked up my boat today 1976 sleek craft 21ft with 460 ford motor and jet drive!   Boo-Ya!

Useless if she can't idle down to 1.5 for walleye. Not my kind of boat but congrats.....looks like a real mover.

Even if he can idle her down, the noise will probably chase away any fish within a half mile.  Have you ever listened to a jet boat wind out on a flat lake? Friend of a friend used to have one with a big Ford in it up north. You could hear him fire it up miles away and then listen to every foot of the very quick trip up the lake. He used to let it out by the moonlight when the lake was really calm.  That was spooky. Not real smart but we were young then, and unbreakable.  JF  JF
Y'all can't fish outta that! Nice ride!
Wicked looking boat man.  What's she worth, if you don't mind me asking?
That's got "Hold my beer and watch this" written all over it !!
Nice, should work well in extremely shallow water.

Well Brad knowing you for around 20 years that sure does not surprise me that you got a boat like that I knew you could never slow down.  Cheers I want a ride I think.  Well we will see how Risty makes out first
